{"type":"message","id":"b7ebc4a4","parentId":"39bb2df4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:20:46.653Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_nnxghwzbtgac_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"    $totalTokens = 0\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($pulse in $script:Pulses) {\r\n        $tokens = [regex]::Matches($pulse.Content, '\\S+') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n        foreach ($token in $tokens) {\r\n            if ($allTokens.ContainsKey($token)) {\r\n                $allTokens[$token]++\r\n            } else {\r\n                $allTokens[$token] = 1\r\n            }\r\n            $totalTokens++\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $scoredTokens = @()\r\n    foreach ($token in $allTokens.Keys) {\r\n        $freq = $allTokens[$token]\r\n        $cfi = Get-CFI -token $token -tokenCounts $allTokens -totalTokens $totalTokens\r\n        $score = Get-HybridScore -cfi $cfi -freq $freq\r\n        \r\n        $scoredTokens += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n            Token = $token\r\n            Frequency = $freq\r\n            CFI = $cfi\r\n            Score = $score\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $scoredTokens = $scoredTokens | Sort-Object Score -Descending\r\n    \r\n    Write-Host \"=== HYBRID CFI×Freq SCORING RESULTS ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\n    Write-Host \"Total tokens analyzed: $totalTokens\" -ForegroundColor White\r\n    Write-Host \"Unique tokens: $($scoredTokens.Count)\" -ForegroundColor White\r\n    \r\n    Write-Host \"`n=== TOP 30 SCORED TOKENS (Research Trajectory Candidates) ===\" -ForegroundColor Green\r\n    $scoredTokens | Select-Object -First 30 | Format-Table -AutoSize\r\n    \r\n    Write-Host \"`n=== CONSTANT FORMAT TOKENS (freq ~160, CFI ~1.0, Score ~0.67) ===\" -ForegroundColor Yellow\r\n    $constantFormat\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 13:19:34\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774372846652}}
{"type":"message","id":"806a1ba8","parentId":"b7ebc4a4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:20:51.124Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The file seems truncated. Let me check the git log from the output and see what was committed. The exec output showed:\n\n```\n[master 0e0eea4] pulse: 2026-03-24 132016\n 5 files changed, 252 insertions(+), 148 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 132016.md\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 131914.mutation (100%)\n```\n\nSo the mutation was moved from proposed to rejected. \n\nThe session file was created but the log output appears incomplete since the read operation only returned 100 lines and didn't capture the full content.","thinkingSignature":"3d0d4642ff5c36d460ef127ed44d43e56d542276888c90be74e878a7272bcf00"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_4fa24tlv8cvl_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"powershell -Command \"Get-Content 'C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 132016.md' -Tail 50\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2749,"output":213,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15099,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774372846655}}
{"type":"message","id":"c510c8e6","parentId":"806a1ba8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:20:52.624Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_4fa24tlv8cvl_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Refined Formula\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) x normalize(freq, min=3, max=120)\r\n\r\nWhere normalize(freq) = clamp(freq/120, 0, 1)\r\n\r\n**For freq=160:** score = 1.00 x 1.0 = 1.00 (still problematic)\r\n**For freq=136:** score = 0.96 x 1.0 = 0.96 (still problematic)\r\n\r\n## Key Insight\r\nThe formula needs a **decay function** that caps contribution from very high frequencies:\r\n\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) x (freq / (freq + k))^n  [Option 1: saturating]\r\nOR\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) x log(freq) / log(160)   [Option 2: log normalization]\r\n\r\n## Experiment Plan\r\n- [ ] Implement log-normalized scoring\r\n- [ ] Apply to all 200 pulses\r\n- [ ] Compare precision/recall against Strategy A (freq-only) and Strategy B (CFI threshold)\r\n- [ ] Find optimal threshold for score(T)\r\n\r\n## Tentative Refined Formula\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) x log(freq) / log(160)\r\n\r\n| Token Type | freq | CFI | score |\r\n|------------|------|-----|-------|\r\n| Constant format | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 x 1.0 = 1.00 |\r\n| \"Phase 1\" | 136 | 0.96 | 0.96 x 0.97 = 0.93 |\r\n| Research trajectory | 60 | 0.75 | 0.75 x 0.84 = 0.63 |\r\n| Noise token | 3 | 0.30 | 0.30 x 0.11 = 0.033 |\r\n\r\n**Still not discriminating enough for freq=160 vs freq=136.**\r\n\r\n## Required: Asymmetric Decay Function\r\n\r\nThe real need is to penalize freq > 120 (constants) while preserving freq < 120 (research):\r\n\r\n```\r\nif freq <= 120:\r\n    freq_score = freq / 120\r\nelse:\r\n    freq_score = decay(freq)  # approaches 0 for very high freq\r\n```\r\n\r\nOr simpler: cap at 1.0, then apply exponential decay ABOVE\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 13:20:39"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1492,"aggregated":"## Refined Formula\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) x normalize(freq, min=3, max=120)\r\n\r\nWhere normalize(freq) = clamp(freq/120, 0, 1)\r\n\r\n**For freq=160:** score = 1.00 x 1.0 = 1.00 (still problematic)\r\n**For freq=136:** score = 0.96 x 1.0 = 0.96 (still problematic)\r\n\r\n## Key Insight\r\nThe formula needs a **decay function** that caps contribution from very high frequencies:\r\n\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) x (freq / (freq + k))^n  [Option 1: saturating]\r\nOR\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) x log(freq) / log(160)   [Option 2: log normalization]\r\n\r\n## Experiment Plan\r\n- [ ] Implement log-normalized scoring\r\n- [ ] Apply to all 200 pulses\r\n- [ ] Compare precision/recall against Strategy A (freq-only) and Strategy B (CFI threshold)\r\n- [ ] Find optimal threshold for score(T)\r\n\r\n## Tentative Refined Formula\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) x log(freq) / log(160)\r\n\r\n| Token Type | freq | CFI | score |\r\n|------------|------|-----|-------|\r\n| Constant format | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 x 1.0 = 1.00 |\r\n| \"Phase 1\" | 136 | 0.96 | 0.96 x 0.97 = 0.93 |\r\n| Research trajectory | 60 | 0.75 | 0.75 x 0.84 = 0.63 |\r\n| Noise token | 3 | 0.30 | 0.30 x 0.11 = 0.033 |\r\n\r\n**Still not discriminating enough for freq=160 vs freq=136.**\r\n\r\n## Required: Asymmetric Decay Function\r\n\r\nThe real need is to penalize freq > 120 (constants) while preserving freq < 120 (research):\r\n\r\n```\r\nif freq <= 120:\r\n    freq_score = freq / 120\r\nelse:\r\n    freq_score = decay(freq)  # approaches 0 for very high freq\r\n```\r\n\r\nOr simpler: cap at 1.0, then apply exponential decay ABOVE\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 13:20:39","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774372852620}}
{"type":"message","id":"03bd6997","parentId":"c510c8e6","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:20:59.526Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. Let me also check the newly created pulse file for the complete observation summary.","thinkingSignature":"660a99b647cdbd4b4c1f1d6aaea2c8c3ba6ef1d683f7011b9d1ef7c29420ecc5"},{"type":"text","text":"Here's the summary of this pulse cycle:\n\n---\n\n**📍 Sandbox Pulse — 2026-03-24 13:20**\n\n**Observation:**\nThe CFI Compression Synthesis identified that the formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` is still insufficient — constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.0) score 1.00, indistinguishable from research trajectory tokens. The key insight: need an **asymmetric decay function** that penalizes freq > 120 while preserving freq < 120.\n\n**Refined formula proposed:**\n```\nif freq <= 120: freq_score = freq/120\nelse: freq_score = decay(freq)  # approaches 0 for very high freq\n```\nOr log-normalized: `score(T) = CFI(T) × log(freq) / log(160)`\n\n**Mutation (REJECTED):** `2026-03-24 131914.mutation` — the initial `hybrid_scoring.ps1` script was filed but not committed. The reason: it used the naive `min(1, freq/120)` cap, which doesn't solve the freq=160 problem. The pulse correctly identified the formula needed refinement first.\n\n**Committed:** New session log + rejected mutation renamed.\n\n**For next instantiation:** 0 proposed mutations. The system is waiting for an implementer to build the asymmetric decay scoring and apply it to the full 200-pulse dataset."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3503,"output":328,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15968,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774372852625}}
